===Transitive verb===
# to [[confuse]]; to [[mix up]], to [[puzzle]]
# to fail to see the diffrence; to mix up; confound right and wrong.
# to make something bad worse: don't confound the [[situation]] by yelling.
# to cause to be ashamed; abash: his actions confounded the skeptics who said he couldn't.
# to [[defeat]]
# to damn: confound you!
# to frustrate: his constant naggin confounded their marrage.
# [[Archaic]] To bring to [[ruination]]. 

[[io:Confound]]

